  <mainDescription>&lt;h3>&#xD;
    User story&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    We use &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../../practice.requirements.user_story.base-sintef/workproducts/user_stories_81DDC5F5.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;_jYx1tA7OEeG7mKurZhyY1A&quot;>User stories&lt;/a> in the NEFFICS project to capture requirements and drive the&#xD;
    implementation work. The&amp;nbsp;initial requirements schema below has been implemented in the&amp;nbsp;&lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../../practice.requirements.user_story.extend_neffics-sintef/guidances/toolmentors/fusionforge_site_79AA1A32.html&quot;&#xD;
     guid=&quot;_O5NgYBEiEeGiNvnvkdqeiQ&quot;>FusionForge: Site&lt;/a>.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;resources/requirements_schema.png&quot; width=&quot;600&quot; height=&quot;314&quot; />&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The schema can be extended&amp;nbsp;later to incorporate some additional elements or relationships&amp;nbsp;if needed. The&#xD;
    solution box consists of:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Solution areas – at least 3 &#xD;
        &lt;ul>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                NEFFICS Platform (generic)&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Vlastuin solution (specific)&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                HSJD solution (specific)&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
        &lt;/ul>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Components – software components that can be configured/integrated/used as part of ONE solution &#xD;
        &lt;ul>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                BOP&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                CPF&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Induct&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                NEFFICS Methodology&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                ServiceML Modelling Tool&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                ...&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
        &lt;/ul>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Features – Functionality/capability of the software components &#xD;
        &lt;ul>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                ...&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
        &lt;/ul>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    With this interpretation of the three solution levels we thought it would be better to associate themes with software&#xD;
    components and epics/user stories with features.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
